Reports from France and Germany would indicate that this is a particularly good time to acquire wines for laying down. The rea- sons are quite simple. The 1949 vintage was a success almost everywhere, but the quantity produced was small. The 1950 vintage was remarkably fine among the white Burgundies and the German wines,
